The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Sunday, November 17, 2002 				 Reuters post
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Nov. 16: Malayala Manorama editor Mammen Mathew has become the first Indian to be appointed as a Reuters trustee  considered to be an honour among journalists world-over.																								Mathew will now be one of the trustees of the Reuters Founders Share Company (RFSC), tasked to safeguard the neutrality and independence of Reuters  the global news agency.																								Welcoming his appointment, RFSC chairman Pehr Gyllenhammar said: We are delighted to welcome Mammen Mathew as a Reuters trustee. He brings a strong background in international journalism and we are sure he will make a valuable contribution to the Reuters Founders Share Company.
